Perform proportional to population size (PPS) sampling based on SMART approach

get_pps.Rd

Perform proportional to population size (PPS) sampling based on SMART approach

get_pps(df, pop, m)

Arguments

df

A data.frame of clusters/villages with their population size
pop

A character value specifying the name of the variable in `df` for the population size information
m

Number of clusters

Value

A data.frame which is a subset of `df` of the selected clusters for the survey sample. A new variable called `cluster_id` is created which identifies the cluster number and the reserved clusters.

Examples

get_pps(df = villageList1, pop = "pop", m = 30)
